posts.content: Hi all. Does anyone know anything about TTE509L. Peppermint bottom white on top RHD 15 window. I believe it's a SA import converted into a camper. Lots of money thrown at it but unfortunately I know nothing of its history. I will contact DVLA for info but please help if you can cheers Johnny.
Sent from my iPad using Tapatalk

Nice looking bus

Info from DVLA. I'm surprised it is down as Manufactured in 1972.

With that pressed VW badge on the front its a "Fleetline" i would guess. 1975 or 76 manufacture.
Not that that particularly helps with finding the previous owners!

Lol. I didn't know about a pressed badge on a fleetline. Thanks


Sent from my iPad using Tapatalk

doubt your gonna find much history TBH…probably hasn't been in the country a great deal of time and finding pre- `UK history will be nigh on impossible

looks like a nice bus though, 75 SA fleet line , RHD, dorm roof (later addition), corner windows…and looks to have been done really well too
Nice bus



but unless you know who imported it…and they know more details about where it came from, your search for history is gonna be a pretty short one

Thanks Maddison. Not sure why people are saying its a 75. Are DVLA wrong when they say it's a 72? I'm in the process of putting on deluxe belt trim, it's running White empi 5's at the mo too. Really good look I think.
